summary.value:
The edits done to this registration are as follows; 
Based on data collected from the pilot study;
* The Cultural Appreciation scale was removed from the survey.
* From the realistic and Symbolic Threat scales, Symbolic Threat items were excluded due to low item reliability. 

* The wording for the vignettes were changed as follows;
              - Limiting diversity condition;
               "With MSU-Texas steadily climbing the ranks due to the university’s growing popularity, affordability, and increasingly competitive programs, the administrators are working hard to ensure the university continues to grow in all aspects. MSU-Texas has been recruiting the brightest students, local and international, for their undergraduate and graduate programs. The University has also been providing funding in the form of scholarships and stipends to further attract students from outside the U.S. who may not otherwise have considered attending MSU-Texas. There has been a change in recent years, however. Due to changes in administration and external events, administrators are now focusing on gaining national recognition by recruiting more local students who are citizens of the United States. Specifically, MSU-Texas will be focusing recruitment efforts in North Texas. This push means that there will be changes made that will mainly affect the international student population.

             Administrators have decided to limit the acceptance of applications from international students for the foreseeable future. Administrators will also be eliminating funding available to international students and instead, put it towards awarding more scholarships to local students. Administrators hope this effort will attract more students within Texas, and from North Texas in particular. "
                     -Continuing diversity condition;
                    "With MSU-Texas steadily climbing the ranks due to the university’s growing popularity, affordability, and increasingly competitive programs, the administrators are working hard to ensure the university continues to grow in all aspects. MSU-Texas has been recruiting the brightest students, local and international, for their undergraduate and graduate programs. The University has also been providing funding in the form of scholarships and stipends to further attract students from outside the U.S. who may not otherwise have considered attending MSU-Texas. There has been a change in recent years, however. Due to the changes in administration and external events, administrators are now focusing on gaining national recognition by increasing recruitment efforts with international communities. Specifically, MSU-Texas will be focusing on increased recruitment efforts in the Caribbean, and in Asian countries. This push means that there will be changes made that will mainly affect the international student population.

             Administrators have decided to increase the acceptance of applications from international students for the foreseeable future. Administrators will be increasing funding available to international students while also supporting students from the North Texas region. Administrators hope this effort will attract more international students. "

*manipulation checks were added to the beginning of the Collective Angst measure;
"To what extent does the new policy proposal at MSU-Texas limit the intake of new international students? "
"To what extent does the new policy proposal at MSU-Texas increase the intake of new international students? ".

Some wording was changed on the modified collective angst measure for clarity. 

* The registration was updated prior to data collection.

